Patricia de Lille is hopeful that the arms inquiry will catch the crooks involved and return tax payers money, but says it should stop asking for money and hopes it doesn't end up like Marikana. JOHANNESBURG - The corruption case against former president Jacob Zuma has been postponed until 23 February 2021. The former president is facing charges of corruption, money laundering, and fraud. READ: Zuma's court case adjourned to September The postponement is to allow French company, Thales to challenge the racketeering charges. Thales is accused of paying bribes to Zuma for 'political protection.'